The paper deals with carrier phase estimation (CPE) methods in optical transmission systems, which involves signal processing and communication theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of laser phase noise and equalization enhanced phase noise, which falls under the category of cs.OH (Optical Networking and Communications). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of bit-error-rate behaviors, which is related to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper involves the comparison of different CPE methods, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Signal Processing).
